  "prompt": "Do I have to shave during a passport appointment?",
  "response": "While there is no strict requirement to shave before a passport appointment, it is generally advisable to present yourself in a neat and clean manner for your passport photo. The photo should clearly show your face, so if facial hair might obscure your features, you may want to consider shaving or trimming your beard. Ultimately, the key is to ensure that your passport photo meets the official requirements, which include having a clear view of your face, without shadows or obstructions.",
